name: Ragnar Trail Snowmass - CO
intro:
Ragnar Trail Snowmass-CO presented by Salomon brings you the perfect fusion of trail running, high-country camping, and Rocky Mountain beauty. Teams of 8 (or 4) will find their inner wild on three separate mountain trails, or “loops" that start and finish at Ragnar Village. Glacial valleys, snowcapped peaks, and blooming wildflowers set the scene as you make your way along rolling single-track. Though you may blame the altitude, in the end it will be the stunning mountain views that take your breath away. Conquer each climb and you'll be rewarded with panoramic views of the Maroon Bells-Snowmass Wilderness — not to mention a much needed downhill. Enjoy world class lodging at Snowmass, or camp under billions of stars with your team at Ragnar Village. We can’t promise it will be easy, but what we can promise is an unforgettable running adventure with friends complete with s’mores, fresh mountain air, and a party atmosphere that Ragnarians have come to love.

Ragnar Trail Snowmass-CO is part of the Double Medal Series. Run both Reebok Ragnar Colorado and Ragnar Trail Snowmass-CO and earn the Rocky Mountain Fever Double Medal.
home:
Ragnar Trail Snowmass-CO presented by Salomon is the weekend adventure you won’t want to miss. Teams of 8 (or 4) will come together in June to conquer a series of three challenging single-track trails that start and finish at Ragnar Village. Push yourself on the challenging hill climbs and you’ll soon be rewarded with views of the Maroon Bells-Snowmass Wilderness and flowy downhill single-track. Between the views of snowcapped peaks, fields of wildflowers and amazingly groomed single-track you will be in trail running heaven. Get ready to celebrate with your team at Ragnar Village where you will enjoy world-class lodging and amenities, s'mores, live music, billions of stars and a party atmosphere Ragnarians have come to love. 

Ragnar Trail Snowmass-CO is part of the Double Medal Series. Run both Reebok Ragnar Colorado and Ragnar Trail Snowmass-CO and earn the Rocky Mountain Fever Double Medal.
village:
Ragnar Village is the heart and soul of the event. Each trail begins and ends in Ragnar Village. It is the Start Line, the Finish Line, and the exchange point. After each loop you will return to the support of your teammates and the adulation of the teams around you. Ragnar Village will be complete with:

  • Bonfire
  • S'mores
  • Music
  • Movies
  • Food & Snacks (Friday night pasta dinner included for each runner)
  • Billions of Stars

Team Staging Area

Each team will be given a location to set up their team campsite in the Ragnar Village. Camping will be located in the plush grass of the Soccer and Softball fields at the Town of Snowmass Village Recreation Center. Awards will be given for the best decorated team campsite and almost anything goes: tents, canopies, couches, camping chairs, BBQ's, kiddie pools full of Kool-Aid, whatever.

We don't assign specific campsites but we do ask that your team takes up less than 300sq-ft.

Race check-in opens on Friday morning. Camping in the Ragnar Village is FREE to runners/family/friends/crew on Friday night. Teams will be allowed into the venue on Friday morning at 8:00 am.

NOTE: No teams will be allowed into the venue before 8:00 am on Friday morning. Note there is no Saturday night camping and everyone must be out of the venue by 8:00 pm on Saturday night.

We ask that all runners camp in the Ragnar Village on Friday night. If you are looking for accommodations in Snowmass for Thursday night before the race or Saturday night after the race, there are options found on our Travel page.

Also, if you are traveling to Ragnar Trail Snowmass from outside the area and wish to rent camping gear for the event, we would suggest you contact the REI Denver store found here: http://www.rei.com/stores/denver.html. Note that rentals cannot be made more than one month out so please plan accordingly.

No dogs on the course. No dogs in the campsite. No dogs at the event. We love dogs too but this is a safety issue for participants and for the dogs.

Please see the Trail Guide for a list of other things that are and aren't allowed in the campsite.

Snowmass Parking/Gear Drop and Shuttle Directions

  • Upon arriving to the race, all cars will be directed into the gear drop area.  Each team vehicle will have their team number written on their rear windshield.  The first team vehicle arriving will be given a parking pass, and designated as “team shuttle car”.
  • Each Team will be given a parking pass to designate 1 car as a “team shuttle car”.  This car will have a parking pass sticker put on the windshield and will be allowed to park down in the rodeo lot near the village.
  • All other team cars must park up the road in the Numbered Lot parking.  These cars will drop their gear and all runners except the driver in the designated gear drop areas, and then drive up to the numbered parking lots to park for the duration of the race.  Follow the directions on the map below.
  • In addition to each “team shuttle car”, which can drive up the road and pick up their teammates from the numbered parking lots, we will also have 2 shuttle vans that will operate during the race.
  • Ragnar Shuttle Van operating hours will be from 8:00AM-4:00PM on Friday, June 3rd, and from 10:00AM-6:00PM on Saturday, June 4th.
  • After cars park up the road in the Numbered Lots, participants can be picked up by their teams “Team Shuttle Vehicle”.  You may also use our shuttle vans during shuttle hours, although our shuttle vans will only help to offset the necessary team shuttles, not completely replace the need for teams to drive up and pick up their team members.

Coexisting with Wildlife

Please help the Town of Snowmass Village foster a community culture of safety and mutual respect by adhering to the following rules:

1.  Don't feed the bears: Please lock your cars, place unattended coolers in a locked car or truck, keep the ground clean of food and drink, and leave no food products inside of your tent.  There will be a storage trailer at Ragnar Village for food and coolers if you wish to store them.

2.  Cross the line, pay a fine: Seasonal trail closures for elk calving are in effect on several Snowmass Village trails until June 21st, some of which are near (but not directly on) the Ragnar Trail Route. Please respect all trail closure gates and signs.

If you have any questions about wildlife in Snowmass Village, please contact the Animal Services Division at (970) 923-5330.

Training by Salomon

At Salomon our goal is to inspire runners to go beyond the pavement and enjoy greater freedom to run anywhere. We believe that with some tips and training almost anyone can become a trail runner and run the Ragnar Trail Relay. We are here to guide you on your training journey as you prepare to run the Ragnar Trail Relay.

charity:
2016 Featured Charity Partner

Ragnar is proud to partner with First Descents as our Official Charity Partner for Ragnar Trail Snowmass-CO. First Descents provides life-changing outdoor adventure programs for young adults impacted by cancer. The First Descents Motto is to be Out Living It, and in true Ragnarian fashion, FD participants take on challenge by choice, seek adventures with friends, and appreciate the power of the outdoors.

Get Out Living It with First Descents! If you would like to receive a free race entry and run with meaning, email outlivingit@firstdescents.org. 

By running with First Descents you are empowering participants to climb, paddle and surf beyond their diagnosis, defy their cancer and connect with others doing the same. For more information on First Descents programs and mission click HERE.

meta_description: Ragnar Trail Snowmass-CO presented by Salomon is the weekend adventure you won't want to miss. Teams of 8 (or 4) will come together in June to conquer a series of three challenging single-track trails that start and finish at Ragnar Village. Push yourself on the challenging hill climbs and you'll soon be rewarded with views of the Maroon Bells-Snowmass Wilderness and flowy downhill single-track.

legs.name: Green Loop - Highline / Lowline Trail
legs.description: You’ll run under the tunnel past your cheering friends at the Team Support Area and head east to the Highline trailhead. This trail runs up to the top of a small ridgeline where you will have an amazing view of the Ragnar Village below and all of the Snowmass Canyon. After one mile of up you will welcome the nice easy rolling down and around back to Ragnar Village.

legs.name: Yellow Loop - Grouse Trail
legs.description: Giddyup, up, up, and up! This awesome single-track trail starts off as an innocent meander down a smooth path and then quickly climbs to over 8500’ through beautiful aspen and pine forests.   As you climb, you’ll get a few flat spots to recover and take it all in before you resume your ascent. Once at the apex, be sure to look out over the valley for an incredible view of Pyramid Peak and the back-side of Maroon Bells. As you descend back towards Ragnar Village, you’ll wish you were back up the mountain again. But don’t worry. You’ll have a few more opportunities to witness the beauty that is Ragnar Trail Snowmass.

legs.name: Red Loop - Rim Trail
legs.description: Going up… again. A short but steep run up a paved road leads you to this amazingly beautiful trail.  You’ll run along the 9000’ ridge overlooking Snowmass and Ragnar Village to the perfect combination of epic views, gorgeous wildflowers, deep dark forests and a long meandering descent.  On the way down, you’ll meet up with your friends from the Rodeo Trail for a run into the Village together.  This is Ragnar Trail at its’ finest.

travel.content:
Special Perks Package

Take advantage of our special Perks Package! You and your teammates can extend your stay with one of our Official Lodging Partners and make it a RUNCATION!

Extended Stay Hotel Accommodations: Bring your friends and family along for a three-night hotel package. They'll have a warm place to stay while you run and you can unwind in some serious luxury!

Express shuttle to and from the race: No need to worry about parking at Ragnar Village. We'll pick you, and your teammates, up from the hotel on Friday! Bring you and your gear to the Ragnar Village, and give you a ride back on Saturday after you finish!

Thursday Night Carb Load Pasta Dinner: You and your team will be served a delicious pre-race meal on Thursday night.

Pro-Runner Workshop and Meet and Greet: Listen to one of our Salomon Pro athletes in person at the Perks Package Dinner!

So how do you get in on this amazing Perks Package? Book your stay with one of our Official Lodging Partners (listed on the left) for June 8th-11th, 2017. 

Hurry, this offer ends May 9th, 2017! 

Westin $297 for all three nights!

Call 1-866-837-4246 and reference "Ragnar Trail Snowmass Perks" Or click HERE to book now!


Holiday Inn Express $198 for all three nights! 

Call 1-855-914-1813 and reference "Ragnar Trail Snowmass Perks". Or click HERE to book now!

 


The Crestwood Lodge

A variety of condo choices from 1-4 bedrooms available for three nights. Pricing ranges from $228 - $486 for all three nights.

To book your room, visit The Crestwood Reservation Page and enter group code RAGNARTRAIL3RDNTFREE for the best rate.

Elevated Legs Rental

Turn your campsite into a recovery station! Our partners Elevated Legs are renting legs for $120 for the whole race - that's $15/person for a team of 8! Don’t forget that you will need a power source. We highly recommend the Goal Zero Yetis.

For more information check out: http://elevatedlegs.com/rent/ragnar/

*Be sure to rent your legs before Monday, May 30th to ensure delivery before the race!*
